<section xml:id="sec-2-2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Arguments</title>
  <p>Arguments are so important, they almost merited their own chapter. Every argument contains a premise, one or more assumptions, and a conclusion.
    An argument is valid when <em>both</em> the premise and the conclusion are true. 
  </p>

